2023 Outdoor World Championships 🌍

Last night @laurenryan____ competed in her first Outdoor World Championships. She fought hard from start to finish in her debut to finish 18th in Heat 1 of the Women’s 5000m 👏🏽🇦🇺

A great experience and a bright future ahead for Lauren 🚀

#BaltimoreDistance #WorldChampionships #Australia #Budapest #UnderArmour #ProtectThisHouse

World Champs Debut ✔️🇭🇺✨
Maybe this race wasn’t the fairytale ending I was hoping for, but I took a risk and this time it didn’t pay off in these championships. This year has been a huge step forward from where I was this time last year. It was a true honour to represent Australia and wear the green and gold alongside an incredible bunch of people, this Aussie 🇦🇺 team is truly something special. 
I am inspired by so many incredible performances and beyond excited to get after it soon. Thank you @athleticsaustralia and @wabudapest23 for an incredible meet, the crowd was electric and wow I cannot wait to be back. 💛💚🦘#wabudapest23 #worldchamps 

📸: (1,3 & 4) @justinbritton (2 & 5) @janfigueroa07

And that’s a wrap @wabudapest23 👊🏽🇭🇺 
Thank you to my amazing support team for getting me here happy and healthy competing on the world stage, I am forever grateful! 💕 I’m so excited for what is next. Leaving Budapest hungry for more✨🫶🏽

& rookie track season is officially in the books ✔️👊🏽✨

Lots of highs, including making my first Outdoor World Champs🇦🇺, Diamond League Debut💎 and a few PR’s on the way. 

Not only this, but a lot of changes. New coach, new brand and a new city🏙️. A huge thank you to @underarmour (@uarunning) 👊🏽🤍 & @missionrun_baltdistance 🚀for welcoming me apart of the team, it’s been an incredible last 6 months and I’m so excited to keep working with this incredible group and brand. Secondly, my new coach @laralu12 thank you for making this season unforgettable and getting me ready for all that we have achieved and I can’t wait for what’s to come!🫶🏽 @coachcarrielane for keeping me healthy and getting me stronger 💪🏽

And huge shout out to my manager @haasruns & @teamtotalathletics for a great year✨

NATIONAL CHAMPION⚡️✨

🎞️: @louiejhadfield

They say good things take time, & 25 years later I can call myself a National Champion.✨💫
What an incredible night it was, doing it in my home country 🇦🇺 with the support of my family & friends. And at the track I’ve been training at for years, I’ve clocked numerous reps at this track with many amazing people who have been apart of my journey (you know who you are & those that have clocked countless miles with me) and I can’t thank you all enough. 💗 Thank you to my team @underarmour & @missionrun_baltdistance 🚀 for supporting me for the past year it has been an amazing first year as a pro, and to my coach @laralu12 thank you!! Lastly a huge shoutout to my manager @haasruns for the continued support & @williamleer for decking me out in some shiny new spikes. Excited to continue this journey and build on the year we have had, thank you for all the lovely messages I have truly felt the support on this journey to my first national title. Love you all ❤️ 
📸: @lightknife.jpg & @michaeldawson.nz
